ðŸ“Œ 1. KpiCard.tsx â€” Conversion KPIs
import React from "react";

interface KpiCardProps {
  label: string;
  value: string | number;
  trendText?: string;
  trendColor?: string;
}

export const KpiCard: React.FC<KpiCardProps> = ({
  label,
  value,
  trendText,
  trendColor = "text-green-500",
}) => (
  <div className="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-sm border">
    <p className="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500">{label}</p>
    <h3 className="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">{value}</h3>
    {trendText && (
      <p className={`text-xs ${trendColor} mt-1`}>{trendText}</p>
    )}
  </div>
);


Usage Example

<KpiCard label="Conversion Rate" value="8.7%" trendText="+0.8% vs last week" />

ðŸ“Š 2. ConversionChart.tsx â€” Chart Container
import React from "react";

interface ConversionChartProps {
  title?: string;
  children: React.ReactNode; // e.g., chart component
}

export const ConversionChart: React.FC<ConversionChartProps> = ({
  title = "Conversion Trend (Last 30 Days)",
  children,
}) => (
  <div className="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md w-full">
    <h2 className="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-4">
      {title}
    </h2>
    <div className="h-64 w-full">{children}</div>
  </div>
);


âš¡ You can plug in a chart here â€” e.g., ApexCharts, Flowbite Charts, or Tremor â€” since all of those integrate with React + Tailwind. 
